'L'alluvione di Firenze del 1966': an ensemble-based re-forecasting ...|https://www.ecmwf.int/en/newsletter/148/meteorology/lalluvione-di-firenze-del-1966-ensemble-based-re-forecasting-study|2016 # ‘L’alluvione di Firenze del 1966’: an ensemble-based re-forecasting study Valerio Capecchi (LaMMA, Italy), Simon Lang, Roberto Buizza (both ECMWF) During the first few days of November 1966, several Italian regions were hit by a storm that produced intense and persistent precipitation over north-east and central Italy. The exceptionally intense rain on 3–4 November followed weeks of wet conditions and led to disastrous flooding. The historical city of Florence (Firenze) was one of the most severely affected. The Arno River flooded the city, causing huge damage to its cultural and artistic heritage and  ...    To mark the 50th anniversary of the Arno River flooding, we have revisited this rainfall event by applying cutting-edge  ...    linear grid with a spacing of about 40 km. It should be noted that the analyses generated then and now incorporate a  ...    accumulation for a set of rain gauges in central Italy. It is worth pointing out that 15 of the 41 reports from the  ...  
